1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
Did you know that more contagious diseases need higher immunity coverage?

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:06,400
Herd immunity thresholds aren't one-size-fits-all.

3
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:08,800
They vary based on the disease.

4
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:12,800
For example, measles needs about 95% immunity to halt outbreaks.

5
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,000
Why so high?

6
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:17,200
More transmissible viruses like COVID-19 require similar thresholds.

7
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:18,800
The data is clear.

8
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:22,800
Understanding these thresholds helps us prepare and protect ourselves better.

9
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:25,600
Stay informed about vaccines and herd immunity.

10
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:27,200
Follow for more insights.
